HEADWORD: Low-church
<hw>Low"-church`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not placing a
high estimate on ecclesiastical organizations or forms; -- applied
especially to Episcopalians, and opposed to <contr>high-church</contr>.
See <cref>High Church</cref>, under <er>High</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Low-churchism</ent>⟦br⟧
